    "descripcionEs": "El sindrome del tunel carpiano es un trastorno musculoesqueletico de origen ocupacional que se produce por la compresion del nervio mediano a su paso por el tunel carpiano en la muneca. Este tunel es un conducto estrecho formado por los huesos del carpo y el ligamento transverso del carpo (retinaculo flexor), por el que pasan nueve tendones flexores y el nervio mediano. Cuando los tejidos circundantes se inflaman o engrosan debido a movimientos repetitivos, posturas forzadas o vibraciones sostenidas propias del entorno laboral, se genera una presion excesiva sobre el nervio mediano que provoca dolor, entumecimiento y debilidad en la mano. Es una de las enfermedades profesionales mas frecuentes en trabajadores que realizan tareas manuales repetitivas, como digitadores, operarios de lineas de ensamblaje, trabajadores textiles, carniceros y musicos profesionales. La prevalencia es significativamente mayor en mujeres, con una proporcion de 3:1 respecto a los hombres, debido a diferencias anatomicas en el tamano del tunel carpiano y factores hormonales asociados.",
    "descripcionEn": "Carpal tunnel syndrome is a musculoskeletal disorder of occupational origin caused by compression of the median nerve as it passes through the carpal tunnel in the wrist. This tunnel is a narrow passage formed by the carpal bones and the transverse carpal ligament (flexor retinaculum), through which nine flexor tendons and the median nerve pass. When surrounding tissues become inflamed or thickened due to repetitive movements, forced postures, or sustained vibrations typical of the work environment, excessive pressure is generated on the median nerve, causing pain, numbness, and weakness in the hand. It is one of the most common occupational diseases among workers who perform repetitive manual tasks, such as typists, assembly line operators, textile workers, butchers, and professional musicians. The prevalence is significantly higher in women, with a ratio of 3:1 compared to men, due to anatomical differences in carpal tunnel size and associated hormonal factors.",
